  "texts": [
    "Finally, the LLM processes the concatenated visual X img and text tokens X text, i.e., [X img, X text], and then autoregressively generates responses Y.",
    "Formally, the language model predicts the response Y = {y i } L i=1 conditioned on the multimodal input X img, X text, where L means the number of tokens in the response.",
    "Therefore, the response is predicted by maximizingp Y | X img, X text = L ∏ i=1 p θ y i | X img, X text, y <i,(1)where θ is the trainable parameters.",
    "Despite the architectural harmonization, the biggest challenge in training generic MLLMs is collecting high-quality visual instruction data, i.e., [X img, X text, Y].",
    "Visual instructions facilitate the alignment of the multimodal (i.e., language-image) space, thus preserving and fusing the knowledge and abilities in the pre-trained vision encoder and LLM, empowering the MLLM with image-based conversation capabilities."
  ],
